																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>Do you want to build a bigger set of arms but find it difficult to schedule those arms day workouts that you know will blow up your physique?&nbsp;</p>



<p>Well, what if I told you that there was a way to create a monster shoulder and tricep workout that would not only condense your time in the gym but also increase muscle growth and recovery?</p>



<p>In this article, we are going to discuss the shoulders and triceps workout, including the benefits, step-by-step exercise tutorials, and professional tips to save you time and maximize muscle growth.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group box-grey is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>Shoulder And Triceps Workout For A Smoking Upper Body</strong></p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#1">Standing Dumbbell Lateral Raises</a>: Targets and isolates the lateral deltoid.</li>



<li><a href="#2">Standing Dumbbell Shoulder Press</a>: Builds front delts and overhead strength.</li>



<li><a href="#3">Standing Dumbbell Arnold Press</a>: Strengthens the front, middle, and rear deltoids.</li>



<li><a href="#4">Lying EZ Bar Tricep Extension</a>: Isolates the triceps.</li>



<li><a href="#5">Seated Dumbbell Tricep Extension</a>: Works the triceps with the additional stability of a seated bench.&nbsp;</li>



<li><a href="#6">Rope Cable Triceps Pushdown</a>: Targets the triceps using the constant resistance of a cable pulley system.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start"><strong>Six Shoulder And Triceps Workouts In 2025</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio youtube-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="The BEST Shoulder &amp; Tricep Workout for MAX Strength &amp; Size!" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VMGUuGSIDvs?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<p>Below are some of the best shoulder tricep exercises for building bigger, stronger arms, including the correct technique, optimal repetition ranges, and more.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="1"><strong>Standing Dumbbell Lateral Raise</strong></h3>



<p>The dumbbell lateral raises are an upper-body exercise that adds width to your shoulders. By lifting the dumbbells laterally out to the sides, you target your lateral deltoids, which will help you sculpt round shoulders.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Lateral-Raise.jpg" alt="shoulder and tricep workout" class="wp-image-12742" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Lateral-Raise.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Lateral-Raise-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Lateral-Raise-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Lateral-Raise-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Lateral-Raise-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Standing Dumbbell Lateral Raise Instruction.
<span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How to do</strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Start by grabbing a pair of dumbbells and stand upright with the dumbbells resting at your sides with palms facing your body.</li>



<li>Gently engage your shoulder blades back and down to make a proud chest.</li>



<li>To begin, lift the dumbbells out toward your sides until your arms are parallel to the floor.</li>



<li>Hold for a moment at the top position and then gradually lower them back down to your sides.</li>



<li>Repeat that movement with good form for the recommended number of repetitions.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Focus on breathing for the duration of the set. Breathing out as you lift the weights and breathing in as you lower them.</li>



<li>Keep your chest up and tense your core muscles for the duration of the exercise. This will provide you with a stable base and improve your capacity to lift the dumbbells.</li>



<li>Maintain a slight bend in the elbow and perform both the lifting and lowering phases of the movement in a controlled motion.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Optimal Sets and Reps</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><td>Training Style</td><td>Sets</td><td>Reps</td></tr><tr><td>Strength Training</td><td>4 &#8211; 6</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td></tr><tr><td>Hypertrophy</td><td>3 &#8211; 4</td><td>8 &#8211; 12</td></tr><tr><td>Endurance Training</td><td>2 &#8211; 3</td><td>15 &#8211; 20</td></tr><tr><td>Power Training</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td><td>1 &#8211; 3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2"><strong>Seated Dumbbell Shoulder Press</strong></h3>



<p>The seated dumbbell shoulder press is an excellent upper-body exercise for increasing muscle mass and strength. It is one of the more popular <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-shoulder-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell shoulder exercises</a> that primarily works the shoulders and engages the triceps by lifting the weight overhead, making it great for developing pressing strength.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Shoulder-Press.jpg" alt="shoulder and tricep workout" class="wp-image-12745" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Shoulder-Press.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Shoulder-Press-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Shoulder-Press-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Shoulder-Press-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Shoulder-Press-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Seated Dumbbell Shoulder Press Instruction.
<span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How to do</strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin by setting your bench to the upright position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Grab your dumbbells off the rack and place them on the floor at the front on the bench.</li>



<li>Sit down on the bench in an upright position with your back flat on the bench and place your feet shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Grab a dumbbell in each hand and rest them vertically on your thighs.</li>



<li>Lift the dumbbells and start the movement by bending your elbows and allowing them to bend out toward your sides.</li>



<li>Then press them directly over your head so that your arms are straight and at the midline of your body without locking out your arms.</li>



<li>Start the movement by bending your elbows and allowing them to bend out toward your sides.</li>



<li>Gradually lower the dumbbells until your elbows are bent at a 90° angle and your upper arms are parallel with the floor.</li>



<li>Once they have reached this position, press the dumbbell back up over your head to the midline of the body without the weights touching.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>While seated, maintain an upright position and engage your core muscles. This will help <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC9952339/#:~:text=The%20core%20is%20particularly%20important,leg%20balance%20and%20athletic%20performance." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">improve core stability</a><sup>[1]</sup> and your ability to press the weight overhead.</li>



<li>Avoid locking out your elbows when the dumbbells are overhead. This will reduce unwanted pressure on your joints.</li>



<li>Keep your wrist over your elbows and your forearm vertical for the duration of the exercise. This will improve your ability to control the dumbbells through the entire range of motion.</li>



<li>Focus on your breathing, inhaling as you lower and exhaling as you press.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Optimal Sets and Reps</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><td>Training Style</td><td>Sets</td><td>Reps</td></tr><tr><td>Strength Training</td><td>4 &#8211; 6</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td></tr><tr><td>Hypertrophy</td><td>3 &#8211; 4</td><td>8 &#8211; 12</td></tr><tr><td>Endurance Training</td><td>2 &#8211; 3</td><td>15 &#8211; 20</td></tr><tr><td>Power Training</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td><td>1 &#8211; 3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3"><strong>Standing Dumbbell Arnold Press</strong></h3>



<p>The standing dumbbell Arnold press is a monster of a shoulder exercise made famous by Arnold Schwarzenegger.&nbsp;</p>



<p>It is one of the great shoulder compound exercises, as it targets the shoulders and triceps and builds overhead strength. It also only requires a set of dumbbells, meaning you can do it almost anywhere, even for those <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/at-home-shoulder-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">shoulder workouts at home</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Arnold-Press.jpg" alt="shoulder and tricep workout" class="wp-image-12748" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Arnold-Press.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Arnold-Press-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Arnold-Press-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Arnold-Press-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Standing-Dumbbell-Arnold-Press-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Standing Dumbbell Arnold Press Instruction.
<span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How to do</h4>



<ol>
<li>In the standing position, grab your dumbbells and, using an underhand grip, curl the dumbbells up so that they are chest height, facing toward you.</li>



<li>Begin pressing the dumbbell upward and simultaneously rotating them so that your palms are facing forward, finishing with arms straight and directly overhead.</li>



<li>Once complete, lower the dumbbells down and rotate them so that they are facing toward you at the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for remaining repetitions.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Press the dumbbells overhead with control, avoid knocking them together, and ensure your elbows finish with a slight bend.</li>



<li>Maintain an upright posture for the duration of the set. This will improve your shoulder range of motion.</li>



<li>Brace your core and exhale as you press the dumbbells overhead.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Optimal Sets and Reps</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><td>Training Style</td><td>Sets</td><td>Reps</td></tr><tr><td>Strength Training</td><td>4 &#8211; 6</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td></tr><tr><td>Hypertrophy</td><td>3 &#8211; 4</td><td>8 &#8211; 12</td></tr><tr><td>Endurance Training</td><td>2 &#8211; 3</td><td>15 &#8211; 20</td></tr><tr><td>Power Training</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td><td>1 &#8211; 3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4"><strong>Lying EZ Bar Tricep Extension</strong></h3>



<p>The lying EZ bar tricep extension is an incredible exercise for targeting the triceps. Fondly known as <em>skull crushers</em>, this exercise uses a similar lying position to a dumbbell bench press and many other chest exercises.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This makes it excellent for isolating the triceps for serious muscle growth, making it a popular choice for any <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/best-tricep-barbell-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">barbell triceps workout</a>.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lying-Ez-Bar-Tricep-Extension-1.jpg" alt="Lying Ez Bar Tricep Extension" class="wp-image-14970" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lying-Ez-Bar-Tricep-Extension-1.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lying-Ez-Bar-Tricep-Extension-1-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lying-Ez-Bar-Tricep-Extension-1-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lying-Ez-Bar-Tricep-Extension-1-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lying-Ez-Bar-Tricep-Extension-1-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Lying EZ Bar Tricep Extension Guide. <span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure></div>


<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How to do</strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Grab the bar hip-width apart with an overhand grip and sit down on a flat bench.</li>



<li>Lie back on the bench and press the bar straight up so they are directly over your shoulders, with your palms facing each other.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the bar toward your head while keeping your upper arm vertical.</li>



<li>Lower the bar until your elbow is bent at a 45° angle and the bar touches your forehead.</li>



<li>Then lift the bar up and slowly return it to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for your remaining repetitions.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Begin with a lighter weight to increase blood flow to the working muscles, and gradually add more weight once you are comfortable with the movement pattern.</li>



<li>When lowering the bar, focus on how your <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/tricep-stretches" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">tricep stretches</a> during the lowering phase and tenses as you lift the bar to improve your mind-muscle connection.</li>



<li>Focus on breathing, inhaling as you lower the weight and exhaling as you lift it back up.</li>



<li>Keep your feet firmly planted on the floor and your core engaged for the duration of the exercise.</li>



<li>It is also a great idea to add this movement to days when you train the chest, as you will already target the three muscle groups: chest, triceps, and shoulders.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Optimal Sets and Reps</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><td>Training Style</td><td>Sets</td><td>Reps</td></tr><tr><td>Strength Training</td><td>4 &#8211; 6</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td></tr><tr><td>Hypertrophy</td><td>3 &#8211; 4</td><td>8 &#8211; 12</td></tr><tr><td>Endurance Training</td><td>2 &#8211; 3</td><td>15 &#8211; 20</td></tr><tr><td>Power Training</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td><td>1 &#8211; 3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="5"><strong>Seated Dumbbell Tricep Extension</strong></h3>



<p>The seated dumbbell tricep extension is one of the best <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-tricep-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell tricep exercises</a> for a shoulder workout. Using two hands to hold the dumbbell behind your head allows for improved control and increased range of motion. Adding a bench with back support also improves stability and allows you to focus on creating a quality contraction with each repetition to maximize results.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Tricep-Extension.jpg" alt="shoulder and tricep workout" class="wp-image-12814" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Tricep-Extension.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Tricep-Extension-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Tricep-Extension-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Tricep-Extension-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Seated-Dumbbell-Tricep-Extension-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Seated Dumbbell Tricep Extension Instruction.
<span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How to do</strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Grab a dumbbell, sit down on the bench, and position your back firmly against the back support.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Using both hands, hold the dumbbell vertically, with each hand supporting the top end of the dumbbell.</li>



<li>Press the dumbbell directly overhead to the starting position.</li>



<li>Begin by allowing your elbows to bend and gently lower the weight behind your head.</li>



<li>Lower until your elbows are bent at 90°.</li>



<li>Then, lift the dumbbell back up until your elbow is fully extended.</li>



<li>Repeat for the rest of the set.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Aim to remain upright with a proud chest and engage your core for the duration of the movement.</li>



<li>Keep your upper arm vertical and your elbows tucked to the side of your head for the duration of the set. This will help you isolate the triceps.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Start with a lighter weight, focus on technique, and gradually increase weight.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Optimal Sets and Reps</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><td>Training Style</td><td>Sets</td><td>Reps</td></tr><tr><td>Strength Training</td><td>4 &#8211; 6</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td></tr><tr><td>Hypertrophy</td><td>3 &#8211; 4</td><td>8 &#8211; 12</td></tr><tr><td>Endurance Training</td><td>2 &#8211; 3</td><td>15 &#8211; 20</td></tr><tr><td>Power Training</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td><td>1 &#8211; 3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="6"><strong>Rope Cable Triceps Pushdown</strong></h3>



<p>The cable tricep pushdown is a popular isolation exercise that is designed to target the triceps. By using a cable machine, there is a constant level of resistance through the entire range of motion, while the pin-based system makes it extremely safe and great for your triceps workout.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Rope-Cable-Triceps-Pushdown-1.jpg" alt="Rope Cable Triceps Pushdown" class="wp-image-14977" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Rope-Cable-Triceps-Pushdown-1.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Rope-Cable-Triceps-Pushdown-1-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Rope-Cable-Triceps-Pushdown-1-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Rope-Cable-Triceps-Pushdown-1-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Rope-Cable-Triceps-Pushdown-1-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Rope Cable Triceps Pushdown Guide. <span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure></div>


<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How to do</strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Standing in front of the cable machine, attach the rope handle to the carabiner and adjust the cable to the highest point.</li>



<li>Reach up and grab the rope with both hands. Walk back slightly so you bend forward at the hip to grab the rope handle.</li>



<li>Pull the rope handle down, and tuck your elbows into your sides so your hands are at shoulder height. Keep a straight back and a proud chest.</li>



<li>Start by pushing the rope down toward the floor until your elbow is fully extended.</li>



<li>Then, gradually allow the rope to return to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your elbows tucked to your sides for the duration of the set.</li>



<li>Avoid using momentum or pushing down with your body weight; this will ensure you are using only your triceps.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Focus on breathing and engaging the core for the duration of the set to improve stability.</li>



<li>This is another excellent exercise to perform when you train your chest, as the safety of the pin-based system can safeguard you.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Optimal Sets and Reps</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><td>Training Style</td><td>Sets</td><td>Reps</td></tr><tr><td>Strength Training</td><td>4 &#8211; 6</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td></tr><tr><td>Hypertrophy</td><td>3 &#8211; 4</td><td>8 &#8211; 12</td></tr><tr><td>Endurance Training</td><td>2 &#8211; 3</td><td>15 &#8211; 20</td></tr><tr><td>Power Training</td><td>3 &#8211; 5</td><td>1 &#8211; 3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start"><strong>Benefits Of Training Shoulders And Triceps Together</strong></h2>



<p>Training your shoulders and triceps is an incredible way to maximize not only your time in the gym but also your growth and recovery time for your upper chest muscles.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Below is a list of benefits and why you should consider combining your <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/arms-and-shoulders-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">arms and shoulders workout</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Better Recovery</strong></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Better-Recovery-endomondo.jpg" alt="Better Recovery" class="wp-image-33119" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Better-Recovery-endomondo.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Better-Recovery-endomondo-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Better-Recovery-endomondo-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Better-Recovery-endomondo-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Better-Recovery-endomondo-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Training shoulder and triceps together free up much-needed time for rest and recovery. <span>Photo: ibrakovic/Freepik</span></figcaption></figure>



<p>Combining your triceps and shoulder days is an excellent way to free up extra time for recovery.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The body requires between <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6719818/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">48 and 78 hours of rest</a><sup>[2]</sup> between training the same muscle groups, which doesn’t leave much time if we train a muscle group each session.</p>



<p>By combining the two into a single routine, you can effectively train muscle groups and free up much-needed time for rest and recovery, which is essential for growth. &nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Save Your Time And Energy</strong></h3>



<p>One of the best things about training your shoulders and triceps together is that you can save time and energy.</p>



<p>Working out takes up a lot of time which can make it difficult to fit into our schedule, however, by training these muscle groups together using a program such as a <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/workouts/3-day-workout-split" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">3-day workout split</a>, you can free up time and energy for life outside the gym.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Helps Increase Your Training Volume</strong></h3>



<p>Adding your tricep exercises to your <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/shoulder-workouts" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">shoulder workouts</a> and training them on the same day is a great way to increase your training volume for both muscle groups.</p>



<p>Your shoulders and triceps are both required during push movements and training them together will allow you to increase training volume, which is shown to <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6303131/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">enhance muscle hypertrophy</a>.<sup>[3]</sup>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading info-heading"><strong>Warming Up And Tips For Safety</strong></h2>



<p>Performing a shoulder and triceps routine is a highly effective way to build muscle and strength, however, precautions should be taken not only to reduce the chances of injury.</p>



<p>Below is a list of warm-up and safety tips to ensure that you have a safe and effective bicep, shoulder, and tricep workout.</p>



<ul>
<li>Perform a three to five-minute warm-up on either the treadmill, elliptical, or rower at a brisk pace to begin your session. This will <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5833972/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">warm up muscle tissue</a><sup>[4]</sup> and increase blood flow to the muscles you aim to target for your session.</li>



<li>Once you have completed your warm-up, perform a light set of your first exercise to prepare your muscles, joints, and nervous system for your first working set.</li>



<li>Before you begin lifting, ensure that you have set safety bars or mechanisms on the piece of equipment you are about to use.</li>



<li>If you are using dumbbells or free weights, have a spotter on standby to help you in case you experience failure during your set.&nbsp;</li>



<li>If you experience pain during your warm-up, workout, or session, consult a healthcare professional to avoid further injury.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading info-heading stop-number-heading"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>



<p>The triceps and shoulders are two muscle groups that fit perfectly together as they often work together for many of our push-day workouts.</p>



<p>By incorporating the two together, you free up valuable time to increase training volume, improve recovery, and enjoy life outside the gym.</p>



